{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-1702"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of corrugated paper and paperboard and of containers of paper and paperboard"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1702"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :corrugated-packaging/plant-operations
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :environmental-stewardship :resource-efficiency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :corrugated-packaging-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "CorrugatedPackagingAdvisor ⊣ Corrugated Packaging Plant Operations
 Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for corrugated-board/box manufacturing
 (corrugator line, printer-slotter/flexo-folder-gluer/die-cutter
 converting lines) -- not direct corrugator/converting-line-equipment
 control authority. Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Eleven concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (any proposal touching corrugator/converting-line-equipment
 control is a hard, permanent block), independent equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-quantity recompute against the batch's own
 logged quantity, double-schedule guard, board/container-grade
 validation, and burst-strength/edge-crush-test plausibility
 validation. Safety-concern flagging (equipment hazard / quality
 defect) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor;
 `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
